  "executive_brief_md": "## CD40 \u2014 CD40 molecule\n\n**White Space score 42.47/100 \u00b7 rank 4/13 \u00b7 HIGH confidence.** Top-tier white space \u2014 validated, tractable, and comparatively uncrowded within the IO cohort.\n\nCD40 is a cell membrane; single-pass type i membrane protein target in the immuno-oncology cohort with no approved drug yet. Development level **Tchem**; mechanism: Tumor necrosis factor receptor superfamily member 5 agonist; Tumor necrosis factor receptor superfamily member 5 antagonist; Tumor necrosis factor receptor superfamily member 5 inhibitor; Tumor necrosis factor receptor superfamily member 5 partial agonist. Competitive footprint: 6 industry sponsor(s) in trials. Leading disease associations: hyper-IgM syndrome type 3, rheumatoid arthritis, Graves disease, inflammatory bowel disease.\n\n**Score decomposition** \u2014 Validation 0.7996, Tractability 0.9, Saturation 0.4099 (cohort-normalized). The score is multiplicative, so crowding drives it down even when biology is validated \u2014 which is why saturated checkpoints sit low and validated-but-uncrowded targets rise.\n\n*Every figure above resolves to a versioned source in the Provenance tab. This brief is model-written (claude-fable-5) over sourced facts only.*",
